 integration installed, turn off transport security by setting the authentication mode and protection level to <ph id=\"ph1\">`None`</ph> as shown in the following sample configuration:","source":"If your computer is not part of a domain or does not have active directory integration installed, turn off transport security by setting the authentication mode and protection level to `None` as shown in the following sample configuration:"},{"content":"Ensure that you change the configuration on both the server and the client before you run the sample.","pos":[5437,5538]},{"pos":[5550,5807],"content":"[!NOTE]\nSetting `security``mode` to `None` is equivalent to setting <xref:System.ServiceModel.MsmqTransportSecurity.MsmqAuthenticationMode%2A>, <xref:System.ServiceModel.MsmqTransportSecurity.MsmqProtectionLevel%2A>, and `Message` security to `None`.","leadings":["","    >  "],"nodes":[{"content":"Setting <ph id=\"ph1\">`security``mode`</ph> to <ph id=\"ph2\">`None`</ph> is equivalent to setting <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.ServiceModel.MsmqTransportSecurity.MsmqAuthenticationMode%2A&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;xref:System.ServiceModel.MsmqTransportSecurity.MsmqProtectionLevel%2A&gt;</ph>, and <ph id=\"ph5\">`Message`</ph> security to <ph id=\"ph6\">`None`</ph>.","pos":[8,250],"source":"Setting `security``mode` to `None` is equivalent to setting <xref:System.ServiceModel.MsmqTransportSecurity.MsmqAuthenticationMode%2A>, <xref:System.ServiceModel.MsmqTransportSecurity.MsmqProtectionLevel%2A>, and `Message` security to `None`."}]},{"content":"To run the database on a remote computer, change the connection string to point to the computer on which the database resides.","pos":[5817,5943]},{"pos":[5952,5964],"content":"Requirements","linkify":"Requirements","nodes":[{"content":"Requirements","pos":[0,12]}]},{"content":"To run this sample, MSMQ must be installed and SQL or SQL Express is required.","pos":[5968,6046]},{"pos":[6055,6067],"content":"Demonstrates","linkify":"Demonstrates","nodes":[{"content":"Demonstrates","pos":[0,12]}]},{"content":"The sample demonstrates transacted batching behavior.","pos":[6071,6124]},{"content":"Transacted batching is a performance optimization feature provided with MSMQ queued transport.","pos":[6125,6219]},{"content":"When transactions are used to send and receive messages there are actually 2 separate transactions.","pos":[6226,6325]},{"content":"When the client sends messages within the scope of a transaction, the transaction is local to the client and the client queue manager.","pos":[6326,6460]},{"content":"When the service receives messages within the scope of the transaction, the transaction is local to the service and the receiving queue manager.","pos":[6461,6605]},{"content":"It is very important to remember that the client and the service are not participating in the same transaction; rather they are using different transactions when performing their operations (such as send and receive) with the queue.","pos":[6606,6838]},{"content":"In the sample we use a single transaction for the execution of multiple service operations.","pos":[6845,6936]},{"content":"This is used only as a performance optimization feature and does not impact the semantics of the application.","pos":[6937,7046]},{"content":"The sample is based on <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Transacted MSMQ Binding<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../docs/framework/wcf/samples/transacted-msmq-binding.md)</ept>.","pos":[7047,7163],"source":" The sample is based on [Transacted MSMQ Binding](../../../../docs/framework/wcf/samples/transacted-msmq-binding.md)."},{"pos":[7172,7180],"content":"Comments","linkify":"Comments","nodes":[{"content":"Comments","pos":[0,8]}]},{"content":"In this sample, the client sends a batch of messages to the service from within the scope of a transaction.","pos":[7184,7291]},{"content":"To show the performance optimization, we send a large number of messages; in this case, up to 2500 messages.","pos":[7292,7400]},{"content":"The messages sent to the queue are then received by the service within the transaction scope defined by the service.","pos":[7407,7523]},{"content":"Without batching, this results in 2500 transactions for each invocation of the service operation.","pos":[7524,7621]},{"content":"This impacts performance of the system.","pos":[7622,7661]},{"content":"Because two resource managers are involved -the MSMQ queue and the <ph id=\"ph1\">`Orders`</ph> database- each such transaction is a DTC transaction.","pos":[7662,7791],"source":" Because two resource managers are involved -the MSMQ queue and the `Orders` database- each such transaction is a DTC transaction."},{"content":"We optimize this by using a much smaller number of transactions by ensuring that a batch of messages and service operation invocations happen in a single transaction.","pos":[7792,7958]},{"content":"We use the batching feature by:","pos":[7965,7996]},{"content":"Specifying transacted batching behavior in configuration.","pos":[8006,8063]},{"content":"Specifying a batch size in terms of number of messages to be read using a single transaction.","pos":[8073,8166]},{"content":"Specifying the maximum number of concurrent batches to run.","pos":[8176,8235]},{"content":"In this example, we show performance gains by reducing the number of transactions by ensuring that 100 service operations are invoked in a single transaction before committing the transaction.","pos":[8242,8434]},{"content":"The service behavior defines an operation behavior with <ph id=\"ph1\">`TransactionScopeRequired`</ph> set to <ph id=\"ph2\">`true`</ph>.","pos":[8441,8538],"source":"The service behavior defines an operation behavior with `TransactionScopeRequired` set to `true`."},{"content":"This ensures that the same transaction scope that is used to retrieve the message from the queue is used by any resource managers accessed by the method.","pos":[8539,8692]},{"content":"In this example, we use a basic database to store the purchase order information contained in the message.","pos":[8693,8799]},{"content":"The transaction scope also guarantees that if the method throws an exception, the message is returned to the queue.","pos":[8800,8915]},{"content":"Without setting this operation behavior, a queued channel creates a transaction to read the message from the queue and commits it automatically before it is dispatched so that if the operation fails, the message is lost.","pos":[8916,9136]},{"content":"The most common scenario is for service operations to enlist in the transaction that is used to read the message from the queue as demonstrated in the following code.","pos":[9137,9303]},{"content":"Note that <ph id=\"ph1\">`ReleaseServiceInstanceOnTransactionComplete`</ph> is set to <ph id=\"ph2\">`false`</ph>.","pos":[9310,9384],"source":"Note that `ReleaseServiceInstanceOnTransactionComplete` is set to `false`."},{"content":"This is an important requirement for batching.","pos":[9385,9431]},{"content":"The property <ph id=\"ph1\">`ReleaseServiceInstanceOnTransactionComplete`</ph> on <ph id=\"ph2\">`ServiceBehaviorAttribute`</ph> indicates what to do with the service instance once the transaction is completed.","pos":[9432,9602],"source":" The property `ReleaseServiceInstanceOnTransactionComplete` on `ServiceBehaviorAttribute` indicates what to do with the service instance once the transaction is completed."},{"content":"By default, the service instance is released upon completing the transaction.","pos":[9603,9680]},{"content":"The core aspect to batching is the use of a single transaction for reading and dispatching many messages in the queue.","pos":[9681,9799]},{"content":"Therefore releasing the service instance ends up completing the transaction prematurely negating the very use of batching.","pos":[9800,9922]},{"content":"If this property is set to <ph id=\"ph1\">`true`</ph> and transacted batching behavior is added to the endpoint, the batching validation behavior throws an exception.","pos":[9923,10069],"source":" If this property is set to `true` and transacted batching behavior is added to the endpoint, the batching validation behavior throws an exception."},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">`Orders`</ph> class encapsulates the processing of the order.","pos":[10737,10797],"source":"The `Orders` class encapsulates the processing of the order."},{"content":"In the sample, it updates the database with purchase order information.","pos":[10798,10869]},{"content":"The batching behavior and its configuration are specified in the service application configuration.","pos":[14381,14480]},{"pos":[16056,16363],"content":"[!NOTE]\n The batch size is a hint to the system. For example, if you specify a batch size of 20, then 20 messages would be read and dispatched using a single transaction and then the transaction is committed. But there are cases where the transaction may commit the batch before the batch size is reached.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":" The batch size is a hint to the system. For example, if you specify a batch size of 20, then 20 messages would be read and dispatched using a single transaction and then the transaction is committed. But there are cases where the transaction may commit the batch before the batch size is reached.","pos":[8,305],"nodes":[{"content":"The batch size is a hint to the system.","pos":[1,40]},{"content":"For example, if you specify a batch size of 20, then 20 messages would be read and dispatched using a single transaction and then the transaction is committed.","pos":[41,200]},{"content":"But there are cases where the transaction may commit the batch before the batch size is reached.","pos":[201,297]}]}]},{"content":"Associated with every transaction is a timeout that starts ticking once the transaction is created.","pos":[16374,16473]},{"content":"When this timeout expires the transaction is aborted.","pos":[16474,16527]},{"content":"It is possible for this timeout to expire even before the batch size is reached.","pos":[16528,16608]},{"content":"To avoid re-working the batch because of the abort, the <ph id=\"ph1\">`TransactedBatchingBehavior`</ph> checks to see how much time is left on the transaction.","pos":[16609,16749],"source":" To avoid re-working the batch because of the abort, the `TransactedBatchingBehavior` checks to see how much time is left on the transaction."},{"content":"If 80% of the transaction timeout is used up, then the transaction is committed.","pos":[16750,16830]},{"content":"If there are no more messages in the queue then instead of waiting for the fulfillment of the batch size the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.TransactedBatchingBehavior&gt;</ph> commits the transaction.","pos":[16841,17040],"source":"If there are no more messages in the queue then instead of waiting for the fulfillment of the batch size the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Description.TransactedBatchingBehavior> commits the transaction."},{"content":"The choice of the batch size is dependent on your application.","pos":[17051,17113]},{"content":"If the batch size is too small, you may not get the desired performance.","pos":[17114,17186]},{"content":"On the other hand if the batch size is too big, it may deteriorate performance.","pos":[17187,17266]},{"content":"For example, your transaction could live longer and hold locks on your database or your transaction could become dead locked, which could cause the batch to get rolled back and to redo the work.","pos":[17267,17461]},{"content":"The client creates a transaction scope.","pos":[17468,17507]},{"content":"Communication with the queue takes place within the scope of the transaction, causing it to be treated as an atomic unit where all messages are sent to the queue or none of the messages are sent to the queue.","pos":[17508,17716]},{"content":"The transaction is committed by calling <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.TransactionScope.Complete%2A&gt;</ph> on the transaction scope.","pos":[17717,17838],"source":" The transaction is committed by calling <xref:System.Transactions.TransactionScope.Complete%2A> on the transaction scope."},{"content":"When you run the sample, the client and service activities are displayed in both the service and client console windows.","pos":[19631,19751]},{"content":"You can see the service receive messages from the client.","pos":[19752,19809]},{"content":"Press ENTER in each console window to shut down the service and client.","pos":[19810,19881]},{"content":"Note that because queuing is in use, the client and service do not have to be up and running at the same time.","pos":[19882,19992]},{"content":"You can run the client, shut it down, and then start up the service and it still receives its messages.","pos":[19993,20096]},{"content":"You can see a rolling output as messages are read in a batch and processed.","pos":[20097,20172]},{"pos":[21622,21755],"content":"[!IMPORTANT]\n The samples may already be installed on your computer. Check for the following (default) directory before continuing.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":" The samples may already be installed on your computer. Check for the following (default) directory before continuing.","pos":[13,131],"nodes":[{"content":"The samples may already be installed on your computer.","pos":[1,55]},{"content":"Check for the following (default) directory before continuing.","pos":[56,118]}]}]},{"content":"If this directory does not exist, go to <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) and Windows Workflow Foundation (WF) Samples for .NET Framework 4<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=150780)</ept> to download all <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[indigo1](../../../../includes/indigo1-md.md)]</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[wf1](../../../../includes/wf1-md.md)]</ph> samples.","pos":[21809,22135],"source":"If this directory does not exist, go to [Windows Communication Foundation (WCF) and Windows Workflow Foundation (WF) Samples for .NET Framework 4](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=150780) to download all [!INCLUDE[indigo1](../../../../includes/indigo1-md.md)] and [!INCLUDE[wf1](../../../../includes/wf1-md.md)] samples."},{"content":"This sample is located in the following directory.","pos":[22136,22186]},{"pos":[22274,22282],"content":"See Also","linkify":"See Also","nodes":[{"content":"See Also","pos":[0,8]}]}]}